{{coord|51.655|-0.398|display=title|region:GB_scale:50000}} {{Infobox Legislature | background_color = gray | text_color = white | name = Watford Borough Council | native_name = | transcription_name = | legislature = | coa_pic = | coa_res = | coa-pic = | coa-res = | house_type = Non-metropolitan district council | body = Watford | houses = | leader1_type = [[Directly elected mayor of Watford]] | leader1 = Dorothy Thornhill | party1 = [[Liberal Democrats]] | election1 = | leader2_type = | leader2 = | party2 = | election2 = | leader3_type = | leader3 = | party3 = | election3 = | leader4_type = | leader4 = | party4 = | election4 = | leader5_type = | leader5 = | party5 = | election5 = | leader6_type = | leader6 = | party6 = | election6 = | members = 37 | house1 = | house2 = | structure1 = | structure1_res = | structure2 = | structure2_res = | political_groups1 = | political_groups2 = | committees1 = | committees2 = | joint_committees = | voting_system1 = [[Plurality voting system]] | voting_system2 = | last_election1 = [[United Kingdom local elections, 2008|1 May 2008]] | last_election2 = | session_room = | session_res = | meeting_place = Town Hall, Hempstead Road, Watford | website = http://www.watford.gov.uk/ | footnotes = }} '''Watford Borough Council''' is the [[local authority]] for the [[Watford]] [[non-metropolitan district]] of [[England]], the [[United Kingdom]]. Watford is located in the south-west of [[Hertfordshire]], in the [[East of England]] [[Regions of England|region]].
The Council consists of 37 elected members. 36 of them represent the twelve [[Wards of the United Kingdom|electoral wards]] of the borough; each of the wards elects three councillors. In addition, the [[Directly elected mayor of Watford|mayor of Watford]] is one of the [[directly elected mayors in the United Kingdom]].
The Council is currently controlled by the [[Liberal Democrats]], who hold 25, of the 37 seats. The [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]] hold 6 seats and [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] and the [[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]] each hold 3 seats. One of the Liberal Democrat seats is the elected-mayor, [[Dorothy Thornhill]].
==Composition== {| class="wikitable" ! colspan=2| Party ! Councillors ! Change |- {{Party name with colour|Liberal Democrats}} | 25 | |- {{Party name with colour|Conservative Party (UK)}} | 6 | |- {{Party name with colour|Labour Party (UK)}} | 3 | |- {{Party name with colour|Green Party of England and Wales}} | 3 | |- ! colspan=2| Total ! 37 ! |- | colspan=4| <small>Source: [http://www.watford.gov.uk/ccm/content/legal-and-democratic/councillors-details/about-your-councillors.en Watford Borough Council]</small> |}
Dorothy Thornhill is the current elected Mayor (Lib Dem) and is the first and sole female directly elected Mayor in the UK.
==Wards== Watford consists of twelve wards.
